    • Method Detail

      • setDnsServers

        public WindowsNetworkAdapterSettings.Builder setDnsServers(java.util.List<java.lang.String> dnsServers)
        A list of server IP addresses to use for DNS lookup in a Windows guest operating system.

        These servers should be specified in the order of preference. If this list is not empty, and if a DHCP IP address is used, then these settings override the DHCP settings.

        . This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. If null, no DNS servers are set.
        Parameters:
        dnsServers - New value for the property.

      • setDnsDomain

        public WindowsNetworkAdapterSettings.Builder setDnsDomain(java.lang.String dnsDomain)
        A DNS domain suffix such as vmware.com. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. If null, no DNS domain is set.
        Parameters:
        dnsDomain - New value for the property.

      • setWinsServers

        public WindowsNetworkAdapterSettings.Builder setWinsServers(java.util.List<java.lang.String> winsServers)
        List of WINS Servers to set for the Windows guest operating system. A Maximum of two IP addresses can be specified in this list. The first IP address will be set as the primary WINS server. The second IP address will be set as the secondary WINS server. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. If null, no WINS Servers are set.
        Parameters:
        winsServers - New value for the property.

      • setNetBIOSMode

        public WindowsNetworkAdapterSettings.Builder setNetBIOSMode(WindowsNetworkAdapterSettings.NetBIOSMode netBIOSMode)
        NetBIOS setting for Windows. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. If null, existing NetBIOS mode will be retained.
        Parameters:
        netBIOSMode - New value for the property.
